#To analyze data for each day of the week
mydata['Weekday']=mydata.index.dayofweek
M=mydata[mydata['Weekday']==0]
T=mydata[mydata['Weekday']==1]
W=mydata[mydata['Weekday']==2]
TR=mydata[mydata['Weekday']==3]
FR=mydata[mydata['Weekday']==4]
SA=mydata[mydata['Weekday']==5]
SU=mydata[mydata['Weekday']==6]

#Plot the hourly data according to the day of the week
plt.subplots(nrows=4,ncols=2,figsize=(12,12))
plt.subplot(421)
M['mains'].plot() 
plt.title('Monday')

plt.subplot(422)
T['mains'].plot() 
plt.title('Tuesday')

plt.subplot(423)

plt.title('Wednesday')

plt.subplot(424)

plt.subplot(425)

plt.title('Friday')

plt.subplot(426)
SA['mains'].plot()
plt.title('Saturday')

plt.subplot(427)
SU['mains'].plot()
plt.title('Sunday')

#stem plot for mains consumption for each day of the year 
mydata['Daily']=mydata.index.dayofyear
df=mydata.groupby(['Daily']).mean()
plt.stem(df['mains'],' ')
plt.xlabel('Time')
